cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image and audio super-resolution, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach uses deep convolutional neural networks to model the conditional distribution of high-resolution output given low-resolution observations, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of multiscale complex wavelets, which are commonly used in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed algorithm for fine-tuning the filters bears some similarities with Generative Adversarial Networks, which is a popular topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
